parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inaccurate fuel level readings can cause the driver to run out of fuel, leading to safety risks, inconvenience, and potential accidents.
symptoms: The fuel gauge displays incorrect fuel levels
showing empty when the tank is full or full when the tank is empty
the low fuel warning light illuminates unnecessarily
and the driver information center displays incorrect fuel levels.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system failures in doors can cause fires, smoke, and overheating, leading to potential safety risks and damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: door locks and power windows malfunctioning
short circuit in the electrical system
and signs of fire damage on the door.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Power window malfunctions can cause inconvenience and safety risks, especially if the window becomes stuck or difficult to operate.
symptoms: and requires manual assistance to operate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Headlight failure can cause reduced visibility, especially at night, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: only high and fog lights available.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Heated seat malfunctions can cause burns and discomfort to the driver and passengers.
symptoms: Heated seat becomes too hot and unable to turn off
causing burns to the leather seat.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Recall Issues and Lack of Parts
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Delays in recall repairs and lack of available parts can cause inconvenience and safety risks to vehicle owners.
symptoms: Vehicle owners are forced to pay for repairs out of pocket
experience delays in getting their vehicles fixed
and are left with safety risks due to unresolved issues.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the window motors and controls can cause windows to malfunction, leading to safety risks, such as being unable to roll up windows in torrential rain, and causing damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: Windows fail to roll up or down

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear air suspension can cause the vehicle to sag, leading to handling difficulties, reduced safety, and potential accidents.
symptoms: Rear end of the vehicle sags

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Trailing Arm Failure due to Rust
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the trailing arms can cause vibrations, loss of control, and potential accidents, especially at low speeds.
The failure of the stability control system can cause the wheels to lock, leading to loss of control, accidents, and safety risks.
The failure of the exterior lighting system, particularly the headlights, can cause hazardous driving conditions, especially at night, increasing the risk of accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Delayed or Unavailable Recall Repairs (Exterior Lighting)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inability to obtain timely and effective repairs for the exterior lighting system recall can lead to prolonged exposure to hazardous driving conditions, potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: manufacturer exceeds reasonable time frame for repair
interim repairs may not be effective.
